## Environment Setup

### Step 1: Install Required Software

#### Windows 10/11

**1.1 Download and Install JDK**
```bash
# Download Java Development Kit 11 or higher
# Option A: OpenJDK 11
https://adoptopenjdk.net/

# Option B: Oracle JDK
https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/downloads/#java11

# Verify installation
java -version
javac -version
```

**1.2 Set JAVA_HOME Environment Variable**
```
1. Right-click "This PC" or "My Computer"
2. Click "Properties"
3. Click "Advanced system settings"
4. Click "Environment Variables"
5. Under "System variables", click "New"
6. Variable name: JAVA_HOME
7. Variable value: C:\Program Files\Java\jdk-11.x.x (your JDK path)
8. Click OK
```

**1.3 Download and Install Android Studio**
```
1. Go to https://developer.android.com/studio
2. Download latest version
3. Run installer and follow prompts
4. Choose "Standard Setup" during installation
5. Install Android SDK, Android Emulator, Android SDK Platform
6. Location: C:\Users\[YourUsername]\AppData\Local\Android\Sdk
```

**1.4 Verify Android Studio Installation**
- Open Android Studio
- Check SDK Manager (Tools → SDK Manager)
- Ensure these are installed:
  - Android SDK Platform 33 (or latest)
  - Android SDK Build-Tools 33.0.1
  - Android Emulator
  - Google APIs Intel x86 Atom_64 System Image

#### macOS

```bash
# Install using Homebrew
brew tap adoptopenjdk/openjdk
brew cask install adoptopenjdk11

# Download Android Studio
# Go to https://developer.android.com/studio
# Download macOS version and follow installation wizard
```

#### Linux (Ubuntu/Debian)

```bash
# Install JDK
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install openjdk-11-jdk

# Verify
java -version

# Download Android Studio from official website
# https://developer.android.com/studio
```

